@deounix - This is an issue tracker, not a support forum. You should post questions like this at https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/autobahnws

If you're using plain WebSockets (not WAMP, which Autobahn|Python also provides) then it's entirely up to you how you do this. WebSocket does not provide any sugar here - you just send on the socket connection to the respective user.

When you use WAMP, then you can post to a topic which is specific to the user (e.g. "com.myapp.user1234.topci"), or use subscriber black- and whitelisting - http://crossbar.io/docs/Subscriber-Black-and-Whitelisting/

